[
    {
        "title": "Intro",
        "content": [
                        {"text": "When working with jQuery, would you prefer:"},
                        {"code": "<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"someFunction();return false;\">test</a>"},
                        {"text": "Or something like:"},
                        {"code": [
                            "$(function() {",
                            "   $('a').click(function() {",
                            "              someFunction();",
                            "       return false;",
                            "   });",
                            "});"
                        ]},
                        {"text": [
                                "I would personally without doubt choose the latter, this is how I love using jQuery.",
                                "Listening to events and modifying the DOM externally from an included script file.<br>",
                                "Now how do you do your server side templating?<br>",
                                "I bet you do something like this (<a href=\"http://grails.org/doc/latest/guide/6.%20The%20Web%20Layer.html#6.2 Groovy Server Pages\" target=\"_blank\">GSP</a>):"
                        ]},
                    {"code": [
                        "<html>",
                        "   <body>",
                        "       <h1 class=\"name\">Hello ${data.name}</h1>",
                        "       <div class=\"numbers\">",
                        "           <g:each in=\"${[1,2,3]}\" var=\"num\">",
                        "               <p>Number ${num}</p>",
                        "           </g:each>",
                        "       </div>",
                        "   </body>",
                        "</html>"
                    ]}
            ]
    },
    {
        "title": "My proporsal",
        "content": [
                    {"text": "What if you instead could have two files, one with the static markup like this:"},
                    {"code": [
                        "<html>",
                        "   <body>",
                        "       <h1 class=\"name\"><h1>",
                        "       <div class=\"numbers\"></div>",
                        "   </body>",
                        "</html>"
                    ]},
                    {"text": "And one with jQuery, just like you are used to:"},
                    {"code": [
                        "$(function() {",
                        "   $('h1.name').text(data.name);",
                        "   $([1, 2, 3]).each(function(i, n) {",
                        "       $('div.numbers').append($('<p>').text('Number ' + n));",
                        "   });",
                        "});"
                    ]},
                    {"text": "This is exactly what nodequery does, all server side!"}
            ]
    }
]

